      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>corrections**Correction of front-page caption Apr 29 with article on livery-cab drivers killed in New York City this year</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A front-page caption last Saturday in a grouping of pictures of livery-cab drivers killed this year in New York City misidentified the borough where Manuel Lopez died. And an article on Monday about the deaths misstated the number of deaths in the Bronx. Mr. Lopez was one of four drivers killed in Brooklyn; four more, not five, were killed in the Bronx, and one in Queens.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>A front-page caption last Saturday in a grouping of pictures of livery-cab drivers killed this year in New York City misidentified the borough where Manuel Lopez died. And an article on Monday about the deaths misstated the number of deaths in the Bronx. Mr. Lopez was one of four drivers killed in Brooklyn; four more, not five, were killed in the Bronx, and one in Queens.</p>
